          <text>
            Streamwalker and Brightbloom exchange what might have been amused glances—could plants do that without eyes? Probably.

            Streamwalker says gently, "We've reviewed your documentation—dietary requirements, rest needs, human specifications. We're prepared."

            ¶

            This is it—the handoff, the goodbye. I'm not ready.

            I ask, "So we just... transfer here?"

            Leafwhisper—leaves rustling with forced cheerfulness—says, "Standard protocol! We'll document the successful Territory One crossing, confirm your condition, transfer guide responsibility to Streamwalker and Brightbloom, and then Rootwalker and I head back home! Very straightforward process—"

            Rootwalker agrees quietly, "Very."

            Scout bounces between me and the new guides, investigating, assessing.

            Brightbloom says, "Your Scout companion is welcome to continue, of course—We've guided sphere-types before. Lovely travelers!"

            Scout bounces approval and returns to my side.

            Streamwalker asks me directly, "How are you feeling? Ready to continue? The terrain changes significantly—more water, softer ground, different navigation challenges."

            I say, "I'm ready— I think."

            Leafwhisper's leaves shimmer. "You absolutely are! Three days of excellent adaptation, you'll do wonderfully in Territory Two—"

            "Thanks," I say. Then, because I need to, I add, "For everything—the information, the patience, the..." (I gesture vaguely.) "All of it."

            Leafwhisper rustles, "Our pleasure! Truly! First human traveler, absolutely fascinating experience—learning so much about cross-species coordination and adaptive requirements—"

            Rootwalker has moved closer and says, "Good traveler. Safe journey."

            My throat feels tight. "You too. Both of you. Thank you for... being good guides. Good team."

            Leafwhisper makes a sound like a pleased sigh. "We'll tell everyone about you—the human who walked through Territory One with excellent endurance and wonderful curiosity—"

            Rootwalker says gently, "Leafwhisper."

            "Right, yes, I'm talking too much again—it's just, it's been really nice having you with us. And I'll miss the questions, Buddy's medical commentary, and Scout's enthusiastic investigations—"

            I step forward and, feeling slightly ridiculous but not caring, touch Leafwhisper's leaves gently. I say, "I'll miss your explanations—all of them. Even the really long ones about soil composition."

            Leafwhisper's leaves rustle with definite emotion. "*Especially* those ones probably!" they add. "Travel well, Kira Voss. Reach Elder Heartwood. Find your answers."

            I turn to Rootwalker. The tall root-structure stands solid and grounded as always.

            I say, "Thank you—for the water, and the quiet, and knowing when to say 'Time.'"

            Rootwalker makes a deep, resonant sound. Then they do something unexpected.
          </text>
