            They walk — I follow the new guides into new territory, leaving Territory One behind.

            But carrying forward what I'd learned — rhythm, trust, the knowledge that temporary teams could still matter.

            That goodbye hurts — because connection is real.

            And that is okay.

            ¶

            The journey continues.

            One territory at a time.

            One team at a time.

            One impossible adaptation at a time.
          </text>
